SUMMARY: Act 3 Theatre presents FREYDE
DESCRIPTION:Experience the continuing story of FREYDE at Act 3 Theatre's 
 newest presentation.\n\nFREYDE\, a woman whose resilience and humour carr
 y her through pogroms\, the Bolshevik Revolution\, two World Wars\, now j
 ourneys to Canada.\n\nWritten\, read and sung by Beth Anne Cole\, with Ma
 rtin van de Ven on clarinet.\n\nPresented at the Performing Arts Lodge\, 
 110 The Esplanade.\n\nTickets are $15.00 at the door (cash only)\; refres
 hments available for purchase at intermission (again\, cash only).
