SUMMARY: FRIDAY PLAYDATES at Young Peoples Theatre
DESCRIPTION:FRIDAY PLAYDATE\n\nFeaturing the musical stylings of Pete Mos
 s and Songs with Nash\n\nIn the Studio November 21\, 2025 – May 8\, 2026\
 nAges 0 – 5 years\nRun Time: 90 mins. including 30-min. song circle\nPay 
 What You Wish (registration required)\n\nPlay\, explore\, and experience 
 a joyful song circle in a comfy space created just for YPT’s very younges
 t audiences! For two Fridays each month\, our Studio theatre is transform
 ed into a cozy playspace with soft surfaces\, sensory-friendly toys\, and
  activities that spark imaginative play and meaningful interactions betwe
 en little ones and their grownups. Unique to this program are special 30-
 minute song circles that fuse music\, drama\, and play\, led by guest art
 ist-educators: Pete Moss and Songs with Nash.\n\nWhat is open playtime?\n
 Open playtime is a period of unstructured play where children engage in a
 ctivities of their own choosing\, without specific rules or guidance. It 
 plays an important role in child development\, helping to foster creativi
 ty\, problem solving\, social skills\, and emotional regulation.\n\nFrida
 y Playdate is a part of Room for Play\, YPT's newest program for young ch
 ildren ages 0 months - 5 years old and their caregivers. Learn more about
  Room for Play here: https://www.youngpeoplestheatre.org/shows-tickets/ro
 om-for-play/ www.youngpeoplestheatre.org/shows-tickets/room-for-play/ htt
 ps://www.youngpeoplestheatre.org/shows-tickets/room-for-play/
CATEGORIES:early-years,toddler-programming,family-fun,early-learners
