SUMMARY: SLNA's Canada Day Celebration 2026
DESCRIPTION:2026 Program:\n\nThe St. Lawrence Neighbourhood Association's
  Canada Day Celebration has nearly doubled in scale and scope for 2026\, 
 compared with the last several years.\nHighlights of this year's Canada D
 ay program include:\n\n  * entertainment all day\, from 11:00 AM to 6:00 
 PM (see schedule below)\n  * the Kids Zone has been expanded and extended
 \, this year from 11:00 AM until 4:00 PM\, including:\n   > t-shirt paint
 ing (free shirts for the kids)\n   > henna and tattoo artist\n   > carica
 ture artist\n   > photo booth\, and more...\n  * a giant cupcake flag (fo
 r dessert)\, and an open invitation to the Canada Day barbecue hosted by 
 St. James Cathedral\n  * an expanded Community engagement and information
  area\, featuring local representatives from all three levels of governme
 nt\, plus SLNA Board members and development\, heritage and waste reducti
 on group experts\n  * year 2 of the Canada Day food drive (cash and food 
 accepted)\n\nEntertainment Schedule:\nThe entertainment program has been 
 extended for 2026\, and will run from 11:00 AM until 6:00 PM. All perform
 ances will take place on the stage of the Michael Comstock Pavilion in St
 . James Park.\nProgram Highlights:\n\n  * 11:10 Bruce Bell - local histor
 ian\n  * 11:30 Ensemble Topaz – south Asian dance\n  * 12:00 Smile Serena
 des - music from Smile Theatre performers\n  * 1:00 Dereck Ayum - steelpa
 n artist\n  * 2:00 Alan Cohen - popular local jazz quartet\n  * 3:00 Red 
 Rhythm & Blues - indigenous indigiblues band\n  * 4:00 Danny Marks - icon
 ic Toronto rocker and bluesman\n  * 6:00 program ends\n\n[Note: Times are
  approximate\; artists subject to change]\n\nJoin SLNA and your neighbour
 s for all or part of the day's events. Bring the kids\; bring your friend
 s\; bring a picnic.\nWe look forward to seeing you there.\n\nwww.slna.ca/
 canada-day-2026.html https://www.slna.ca/canada-day-2026.html
CATEGORIES:
