SUMMARY: 2026 UpFRONT Festival of Indigenous Arts\, Music & Culture
DESCRIPTION:Announcing TO Live’s 2026 UpFRONT Festival of Indigenous Arts
 \, Music & Culture\, taking place from August 14–16\, 2025.\n\nUpFRONT is
  a weekend-long celebration of Indigenous talent from across Turtle Islan
 d and beyond\, featuring three days of exceptional music\, comedy\, puppe
 try\, free workshops\, and community programming in the heart of Tkaronto
 . All programming is free and open to the public.\n\nIn association with 
 the festival\, TO Live will be installing a temporary outdoor stage and c
 losing Scott Street from Front Street East to Scott Lane. This location w
 ill serve as one of two performance stages\, showcasing Indigenous artist
 s from across Canada at no cost to attendees. This will require the tempo
 rary closure of this section of Scott Street to motor vehicles. Front Str
 eet will remain open to ongoing traffic.\n\nIn addition\, there will be a
  pedestrian Indigenous marketplace along Scott Street from Front Street t
 o Wellington Street and throughout Berczy Park. This marketplace will fea
 ture Indigenous artisan vendors\, food trucks\, pop-up food tents. As par
 t of this activation\, Scott Street south of the public parking lot will 
 also be closed to motor vehicles. Neither of the Public parking lots on S
 cott Street will be blocked.\n\nAlongside the marketplace\, the existing 
 platform within Berczy Park will become a second performance stage to ful
 ly animate the park and surrounding area.\n\nStreet closures will commenc
 e at 12:00 a.m. on August 14\, 2025\, and remain in effect until 11:59 p.
 m. on August 16\, 2025.\n\nProgramming hours will be approximately 12:00 
 p.m.–10:00 p.m. on August 14\, and 10:00 a.m.–10:00 p.m. on August 15 and
  16.\n\nTO Live welcomes the St. Lawrence community to this free and incl
 usive celebration of Indigenous arts and culture. Additional information 
 will be added as it becomes available.
